# AI Model Routing (CoC Engine)

**Scope:** Cursor **development-time** agent routing only. Do **not** change runtime in-game LLM (`js/ai/network.mjs`, DeepSeek API).

Full workflow: `docs/AI_MODEL_WORKFLOW.md`.

## Autonomous routing

**The agent MUST choose the model itself.** The user does **not** need to name Fable 5 / Composer 2.5 / GPT-5.5 on every task.

1. **Infer from task + file paths** â€” use the tables below (and escalate signals) on every assignment.
2. **Delegate with `model`** â€” when spawning Task subagents, pass the matching slug; do not leave routing implicit on subagents.
3. **Brief note only if non-obvious** â€” mention the chosen model in the reply only when the choice is ambiguous, cross-cutting, or the user explicitly asked why.

Default: follow path ownership. Cross-cutting work â†’ parent plans, spawn one subagent per layer with the correct `model`.

## Model slugs (Task subagent `model` param)

| Role | Slug | Use for |
|------|------|---------|
| Fable 5 | `claude-fable-5-thinking-high` | Scenario outlines, Lovecraftian scenes, art direction, narrative design |
| Composer 2.5 Fast | `composer-2.5-fast` | UI code, bulk dialogue/text entry, mechanical components |
| GPT-5.5 | `gpt-5.5-medium` | Sanity, dice, save structures, engines, persistence, KP logic |

## Path â†’ preferred model

| Paths / globs | Model |
|---------------|-------|
| `js/data/scenarios/**`, `js/data/campaigns/**`, `js/data/ai_prompt_config.mjs`, `docs/archive/CCGS*`, creative docs | Fable 5 |
| `js/components/**`, `js/views/**`, `css/**`, `index.html`, `icons/**`, UI docs | Composer 2.5 |
| `js/engines/**`, `js/state/**`, `js/campaign/kp_*.mjs`, `js/campaign/*_engine*`, `js/tools/**`, `tests/**`, `js/scenario/store.mjs`, `js/scenario/runner.mjs` | GPT-5.5 |

## When to use Task subagent with explicit `model`

- **Cross-cutting or large scope** (e.g. new KP rule + UI + scenario text): parent agent plans; spawn focused subagents per layer with matching `model`.
- **Wrong model for the file**: delegate that slice via Task + `model`, not mixed edits in one pass.
- **Creative burst** (scene bible, module pitch): Task + `claude-fable-5-thinking-high`, `readonly: true` for brainstorm-only.
- **Bulk content** (10+ NPC lines, tab labels): Task + `composer-2.5-fast`.
- **Engine correctness** (sanity edge case, save migration, dice resolution): Task + `gpt-5.5-medium`.

Example:

```
Task(subagent_type="generalPurpose", model="gpt-5.5-medium", prompt="Fix sanity tick in js/engines/sanity.mjs â€¦")
```

## Escalate to harder model

| Signal | Escalate to |
|--------|-------------|
| Narrative tone, mythos, KP voice, module structure | Fable 5 |
| Layout, a11y, CSS tokens, component wiring | Composer 2.5 |
| State invariants, migrations, combat/sanity math, KP execution | GPT-5.5 |

## Do not route here

- `js/ai/network.mjs`, `js/ai/worker*.js`, `js/ai_logic.mjs` â€” runtime AI transport; separate from Cursor model choice unless explicitly refactoring dev tooling.
